<item>
            <title>[FELIX-3087] Given invalid value, but the property isn&apos;t invalid.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-3087</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Given the following XML, the value of the property will be invalid.&lt;br/&gt;
But this property is a valid property, with a value of char &apos;a&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;scr:component xmlns:scr=&quot;http://www.osgi.org/xmlns/scr/v1.1.0&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;implementation class=&quot;DummyClass&quot; /&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;property name=&quot;test.property.Character&quot; type=&quot;Character&quot; value=&quot;ab&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/scr:component&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12520111">FELIX-3087</key>
            <summary>Given invalid value, but the property isn&apos;t invalid.</summary>
